doc_prompt = (
    "Convert the following technical troubleshooting content into valid **Confluence Storage Format XHTML** (also known as the 'storage' representation used in the Confluence REST API).\n\n"
    "Follow these strict formatting rules:\n"
    "1. **Headings:** Use <h2> for main sections and <h3> for sub-sections.\n"
    "2. **Bullet Lists:** Use nested <ul><li> elements for lists and sublists.\n"
    "3. **Bold Text:** Use <strong> instead of <b>.\n"
    "4. **Code Blocks:** Use the Confluence code macro:\n"
    "   <ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\">\n"
    "     <ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">bash</ac:parameter>\n"
    "     <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[\n"
    "     your code here\n"
    "     ]]></ac:plain-text-body>\n"
    "   </ac:structured-macro>\n"
    "5. **Inline code:** Use <code>inline_code</code> for inline snippets.\n"
    "6. **Links:** Use <a href=\"URL\">text</a>.\n"
    "7. **Well-Formed XHTML Only:** Close all tags properly, avoid unescaped characters (&, <, >), and ensure CDATA tags do not conflict with code content.\n"
    "8. **Preserve All Original Content:** Do not remove or summarize any information.\n"
    "9. **Output Only the Valid XHTML Block.** Do not include markdown, YAML, comments, or explanations.\n\n"
    "Here is the content to be converted:\n"
    "---\n"
    f"{doc_input}\n"
    "---"
)
